@startuml
' ==============================================================
' CU05 - Emitir Voto
' Votante autenticado emite su voto en Hyperledger Fabric
' ==============================================================
title CU05 - Emitir Voto

skinparam objectBorderColor #005A9C
skinparam objectBackgroundColor #EBF2FF
skinparam objectFontName Arial
skinparam objectFontSize 11
skinparam noteBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFFF0

' ── Participantes ─────────────────────────────────────────────
object "Votante\n<<actor>>" as VOT

object "<<boundary>>\nVotingPage\n(multi-papeleta)" as VP

object "<<control>>\n:FabricController\nPOST /fabric/vote" as CTRL

object "<<control>>\n:UserService\nassertCanVote()" as USVC

object "<<control>>\n:FabricService\nemitirVoto()" as FSVC

object "<<control>>\n:FabricSDK\n(Fabric Gateway)" as SDK

object "<<entity>>\nFabricPeer\npeer0.ficct.edu.bo:7051" as PEER

object "<<entity>>\nChaincode\nevoting-cc" as CC

object "<<control>>\n:UserService\nmarkAsVoted()" as MARK

object "<<entity>>\n:DatabaseService\n(pg Pool)" as DB

object "<<entity>>\nPostgreSQL\nrecibos_voto\npadron_electoral" as PG

' ── Paso 1: Verificar elegibilidad ────────────────────────────
VOT -- VP : 1: seleccionarCandidato(candidatoId)\n+ confirmarVoto()

VP -- CTRL : 2: POST /fabric/vote\n{electionId, candidateId}\n+ JWT Header

CTRL -- USVC : 3: assertCanVote(userId, electionId)
USVC -- DB : 3.1: query("SELECT habilitado\nFROM usuarios WHERE id=?")
DB -- PG : 3.2: executeSQL()
PG -- DB : 3.3: {habilitado: true}
USVC -- DB : 3.4: query("SELECT 1 FROM recibos_voto\nWHERE id_eleccion=? AND id_usuario=?\nAND estado='CONFIRMADO'")
DB -- PG : 3.5: executeSQL()
PG -- DB : 3.6: (sin filas → puede votar)
DB -- USVC : 3.7: ok
USVC -- CTRL : 3.8: autorizado

' ── Paso 2: Emitir voto en Fabric ─────────────────────────────
CTRL -- FSVC : 4: emitirVoto(electionId, candidateId, userId)

FSVC -- SDK : 5: submitTransaction("EmitirVoto",\nvoteId_uuid, electionId, candidateId)

SDK -- PEER : 6: endorseTransaction(propuesta)
PEER -- CC : 7: invoke("EmitirVoto",\nvoteId, electionId, candidateId)
CC -- PEER : 8: {txId, voteId} aprobado
PEER -- SDK : 9: endorsedProposal

SDK -- PEER : 10: commitTransaction()
PEER -- SDK : 11: txId confirmado en ledger

SDK -- FSVC : 12: {txId, voteId}
FSVC -- CTRL : 13: {txId, voteId}

' ── Paso 3: Marcar como votado (anti-doble-voto) ──────────────
CTRL -- MARK : 14: markAsVoted(userId, electionId)
MARK -- DB : 15: transaction: BEGIN\nSELECT ... FOR UPDATE\n(upsert padron_electoral)\nCOMMIT
DB -- PG : 16: executeSQL (SELECT FOR UPDATE)
PG -- DB : 17: lock + rowUpdated
DB -- MARK : 18: ok
MARK -- CTRL : 19: votante marcado

' ── Paso 4: Guardar recibo de voto ────────────────────────────
CTRL -- FSVC : 20: saveSyncLog(electionId, userId,\ncandidateId, txId, voteId, 'CONFIRMADO')
FSVC -- DB : 21: query("INSERT INTO recibos_voto\n(id_eleccion, id_usuario, id_candidato,\ntx_id, voto_id, estado)\nVALUES (..., 'CONFIRMADO')")
DB -- PG : 22: executeSQL()
PG -- DB : 23: recibo creado
DB -- FSVC : 24: recibo

FSVC -- CTRL : 25: {txId, voteId}
CTRL -- VP : 26: 200 OK {txId, voteId, message}
VP -- VOT : 27: "Voto registrado.\nGuarda tu txId para verificar."

note bottom of FSVC
  Anti-doble-voto en 3 capas:
  1. assertCanVote()        → lectura rápida pre-check
  2. SELECT FOR UPDATE      → bloqueo pesimista en transacción
  3. UNIQUE(id_eleccion, id_usuario) en recibos_voto → constraint DB

  Si Fabric falla (paso 5-11):
  → saveSyncLog() con estado=FALLIDO
  → markAsVoted() NO se invoca
  → votante puede reintentar
  → ServiceUnavailableException si Fabric está offline
end note

@enduml
